== Safety ==
Following [[crash testing]] in 2019, the Model 3 performed very well, receiving five stars in every category from the [[National Highway Traffic Safety Administration]]<ref name="lambert-20180920">{{cite news|url=https://electrek.co/2018/09/20/tesla-model-3-5-star-safety-rating-nhtsa/|title=Tesla Model 3 gets perfect 5-star safety rating in every category from NHTSA|work=Electrek|first=Fred|last=Lambert|date=September 20, 2018|access-date=September 20, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920130126/https://electrek.co/2018/09/20/tesla-model-3-5-star-safety-rating-nhtsa/|archive-date=September 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite report|url=https://www.nhtsa.gov/vehicle/2018/TESLA/MODEL%2525203/4%252520DR/RWD|title=2018 Tesla Model 3 4|trans-title=2018 Tesla Model 3 Four-Door Rear Wheel Drive|publisher=[[National Highway Traffic Safety Administration]]|access-date=September 20, 2018|quote=5 stars|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180920193633/https://www.nhtsa.gov/vehicle/2018/TESLA/MODEL%203/4%20DR/RWD|archive-date=September 20, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and a 94% [[Euro NCAP]] score in [[active safety]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Tesla, Mercedes and Škoda Score a Touchdown in Euro NCAP's Latest Safety Tests |url=https://www.euroncap.com/en/press-media/press-releases/tesla-mercedes-and-skoda-score-a-touchdown-in-euro-ncap-s-latest-safety-tests-1/ |website=euroncap.com |publisher=[[Euro NCAP]] |language=en |date=July 3, 2019 |access-date=July 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704070332/https://www.euroncap.com/en/press-media/press-releases/tesla-mercedes-and-skoda-score-a-touchdown-in-euro-ncap-s-latest-safety-tests-1/ |archive-date=July 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Schmidt |first1=Bridie |title=Tesla Model 3 smashes European NCAP tests with best safety assist |url=https://thedriven.io/2019/07/04/tesla-model-3-smashes-european-ncap-tests-with-best-safety-assist/ |website=The Driven |date=July 4, 2019 |quote=(Table sorted ny Safety Assist) |access-date=July 4, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704070350/https://thedriven.io/2019/07/04/tesla-model-3-smashes-european-ncap-tests-with-best-safety-assist/ |archive-date=July 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>
